The paper discusses a competition focused on adversarial examples and robustness of machine learning classifiers, which are topics that are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and computer security (cs.CR). The competition also involves developing new methods to generate adversarial examples and defend against them, which are tasks that are relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
